Behind the boathouse, I'll show you my dark secret."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uvaldayana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valdayana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ruler of Quellious</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(12/25/01 4:08:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogre/troll SKs unite!</span><hr size=1> *Pokes Groshuk* Would you be willing to give up your higher HP total, innate regeneration, and ability to Slam/Bash without needing a shield equipped to be able to use this mask?  Maybe you would, maybe you wouldn't, I don't know.. but every race/class combination has their own advantages and disadvantages, whether it's the quests they can do, the stats they start with, their factions, or in this case, the items they can equip.  Whenever an expansion is released or a zone is revamped, new items show up and people who can't use them will complain.. the theory being that if you knew what the items were in advance, you would have chosen so-and-so class instead of what you did play.  While I don't know the item in question here, how easy it is to get, or much of any shadowknight issue, I can tell you that you're no weaker post-Luclin than you were pre-Luclin, nor is any other class.  You do have new abilities (whether you think they're any good or not) and new spells (ditto), along with whatever other new items are out there for you to claim.  If small race shadowknights get a nice item, you should be happy for them, and when large race shadowknights get a nice item they should be happy for you.  New items make players more powerful, and as we're not on a PvP server, you don't have to worry about competing with the other players.  Power to the players, thus, is a good thing.<br>
<br>
And if you still don't like it, you can remake a human or iksar or whatever smaller shadowknight, but when a nice troll/ogre shadowknight only necklace with Aura of Battle or Marvelous Visions drops, you'll probably just become envious again. *Poke*<br>
