Behind the boathouse, I'll show you my dark secret."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uvaldayana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valdayana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ruler of Quellious</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(12/25/01 9:06:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buck up, chap</span><hr size=1> I admitted I don't have a shadowknight and don't know about their issues, though as a class I prefer them as a tank to other truly useless classes as paladins (who may have decent skill sets and whatnot, but also have those disgusting moral issues that make them worthless).  My statement still stands though, and I'd reference it with examples except I don't know all the details. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But I'll try.. there's a shadowknight one-handed weapon that drops in the Plane of Hate for small race shadowknights, and a two-hander for large races.  With the new Alternate Advancement skills that allow shadowknights to bash without a shield (I'll assume it exists since you hinted at it), the small shadowknights would be upset because they'd want access to the better damaging two-hander from Hate that the large shadowknights can use, as they're not longer forced to use the sword/shield combo to bash.  Of course, the small shadowknights aren't complaining, because there's other items in other zones that fill the void.  Perhaps there's a similar item in another zone to the Feign Death mask for bigger shadowknights.. more likely, as mentioned earlier, it's going to be nerfed with a 3 or 4 second (or more) cast time, now that people are starting to raise a fuss (and I agree that monks likely will be complaining too).  It goes back to the advantages and disadvantages..<br>
<br>
I see the point you're trying to make about wanting access to an item that prevents you from dying, but that doesn't really apply to me because I like to take stupid risks (like tanking in the Halls of Testing) and see exactly how far I can push my fragile form.  But forgetting that.. yeah, most enchanters would like to have an item that casts Dazzle in 3.2 seconds and has an instant recast (which Dazzle normally doesn't have), or an item that casts a Colour stun in 2.5 seconds and has no recast.  But even if such items came out and were restricted to, say, high elf enchanters (because they're the wussiest, of course), it wouldn't really bother me because it doesn't take anything away from my personal skills at playing, and also because I know that if I raise a big ruckus, the item would likely be nerfed and then everyone (high elf and dark elf alike) would be back to square one.  If an item is so powerful that people without it complain, then in the views of the designers, it's probably too powerful for the game.  Whether that's right or wrong isn't my place to judge (though I'm inclined to say it'd be right, if the complaints are truly valid).<br>
<br>
And one last thing since it was brought up.. I want more spell slots too!  I have to swap too much.. especially with the new agro/deagro spells that everyone wants to try out.  &quot;Okay, use the agro boost on the main tank.. then when we do a tank switch, deagro the old tank and agro the new one.. and don't forget to Tash, and redo Clarity on these groups, and have mez up in case we get adds, some will require Rapture, a big charm might help turn the tide, and I really want Gift of Brilliance and Enlightenment and Visions of Grandeur, not Shissar!&quot; All that makes it hard for me to keep Curse of the Simple Mind memorized.. but it still is, because nothing beats seeing the emote &quot;King Tormax looks stupid&quot;. *Looks innocent*<br>
